<!-- Body -->
<refsynopsisdiv>
<cmdsynopsis>
<command>&dhpackage;</command>
 <arg>--version</arg>
 <arg>-h</arg>
 <arg>-v</arg>
 <arg>-q</arg>
 <arg>-d</arg>
 <arg>-f</arg>
 <arg>-c <replaceable>file</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>Description</title>
    <para><emphasis>
This Man page explains the use of <command>&dhpackage;</command>
command line and its options. An agent in OSSIM is set of python
script that gathers and sends the output of the different plugin
or tool to the correlation engine for further process.
    </emphasis></para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1><title>Options</title>
    <para>Here's a description of each options :</para>
    <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--version</option></term>
        <listitem>
        <para>Show program's version number and exit</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-h</option></term>
        <term><option>--help</option></term>
        <listitem>
        <para>Show the list of arguments of the command and exit</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-v</option></term>
        <term><option>--verbose</option></term>
        <listitem>
        <para>Make lots of noise</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-q</option></term>
        <term><option>--quiet</option></term>
        <listitem>
        <para>don't show debug messages [default]</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-f</option></term>
        <term><option>--force</option></term>
        <listitem>
        <para>Force startup overriding pidfile</para>
        </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-c</option><replaceable>file</replaceable></term>
        <term><option>--config=</option><replaceable>file</replaceable></term>
        <listitem>
        <para>read config from file. By default the file should be in
/etc/ossim/agent/config.xml. Read it for more infos the configuration.</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
<para>&hellip;</para>
</refsect1>
